{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2015-2-18-angularjs-jsamine-spies-and-fakes/2015-2-18-angularjs-jsamine-spies-and-fakes/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Its my Code Blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"4572ab77-a085-5f40-90d0-4c452977a26f","excerpt":"One of the great things about angular is it’s testability. Say we have a directive that uses geolocation to display this information to the user if it is…","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/100578ec9732f6883289343f77724c15/7459a/spiesandfakes.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 72.8125%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text \"\n        title=\"AngularJS Jasmine Spies and Fakes\"\n        src=\"/static/100578ec9732f6883289343f77724c15/88218/spiesandfakes.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/100578ec9732f6883289343f77724c15/7237a/spiesandfakes.jpg 148w,\n/static/100578ec9732f6883289343f77724c15/0cfdf/spiesandfakes.jpg 295w,\n/static/100578ec9732f6883289343f77724c15/88218/spiesandfakes.jpg 590w,\n/static/100578ec9732f6883289343f77724c15/7459a/spiesandfakes.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h1>One of the great things about angular is it’s testability.</h1>\n<p>Say we have a directive that uses geolocation to display this information to the user if it is available\nand to display a message if it is not available.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/NicholasMurray/a522f0fae5eb654c9a5a.js\"></script>\n<p>So how can we test it using Jasmine and ensure that our test will work regardless if geolocation is\navailable during our testing? We create a spy on the geolocation function and return a fake object instead.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/NicholasMurray/baeb1de0d4fcffe2fbe9.js\"></script>\n<p>Similarly we can return a fake error object to test that our directive acts correctly if geolocation\nis not available.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/NicholasMurray/78f1c7be22715622f4ff.js\"></script>","frontmatter":{"title":"AngularJS Jasmine Spies and Fakes","date":"February 18, 2015","description":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/2015-2-18-angularjs-jsamine-spies-and-fakes/2015-2-18-angularjs-jsamine-spies-and-fakes/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2015-2-7-psst-wanna-monkey-patch/2015-2-7-psst-wanna-monkey-patch/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Psst! Wanna Monkey Patch?"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2015-2-28-the-zen-of-python/2015-2-28-the-zen-of-python/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"The Zen of Python"}}}}}